21:21.252 --> 21:29.282
And what God will do is He'll leave you in a place long enough where you realize that more than anything you'll know that you're weak.

21:30.284 --> 21:35.250
Those times when you fall in your face and you cry out to God, oh Lord, here's what I'm facing.

21:35.330 --> 21:36.351
Here's what I'm feeling.

21:36.592 --> 21:38.053
Here's what's coming from the devil.

21:38.334 --> 21:39.415
Here's my weakness.

21:39.695 --> 21:40.676
Here's where I'm at.

21:40.997 --> 21:42.599
I need somebody strong.

21:43.039 --> 21:48.406
If you ever find out how weak you are, you'll be able to find out how strong he is.

21:48.886 --> 21:51.830
Paul learned that lesson when he pleaded for his thorn to be removed.

21:52.170 --> 21:53.852
God didn't take his weakness away.

21:54.193 --> 21:55.454
Instead, he gave him a promise.

21:55.775 --> 21:57.797
My grace is sufficient for thee.

21:58.258 --> 22:01.161
My strength is made perfect in weakness.

22:01.662 --> 22:03.764
God doesn't merely just tolerate weakness.

22:04.105 --> 22:05.106
He uses it.

22:05.218 --> 22:06.880
Weakness teaches us to pray.

22:07.161 --> 22:08.763
Weakness teaches us to lean.

22:09.064 --> 22:12.569
Weakness teaches us that power belongs to God.

22:12.909 --> 22:18.858
And when God grants strength, it's not so we can boast, but it's so we can serve.

22:19.700 --> 22:22.283
He strengthens us to lift others up.

22:23.205 --> 22:31.617
Just as J. Beshgili had lifted Saul, some of the strongest ministries are born in the deepest valleys.

22:32.899 --> 22:34.802
Some of the most useful servants for

22:35.074 --> 22:39.240
are those who remembered what it's like to be helpless.

22:41.142 --> 22:43.645
Our weakness isn't a disqualification.

22:43.746 --> 22:45.047
It's a platform for grace.

22:45.949 --> 22:47.891
Your strength is not an achievement.

22:48.832 --> 22:50.314
It's a stewardship from God.

22:51.075 --> 22:52.958
And every season, the message is the same.

22:54.159 --> 22:54.780
Trust him.

22:55.882 --> 22:57.504
When you are weak, he's strong.

22:57.864 --> 23:00.969
When you are strong, he must remain first.

23:01.750 --> 23:05.074
Our hope is not in the condition of our lives, but in the faithfulness

23:05.794 --> 23:06.415
to our Lord.

23:08.217 --> 23:20.312
Remember Elijah talking a couple weeks ago about his dad and grandpa taking him hunting and teaching him the path, how to get out there.

23:21.273 --> 23:23.055
They were making him strong.

23:23.556 --> 23:27.180
That's what we want to do for our kids is make them strong.

23:28.522 --> 23:33.007
I remember the first time somebody took me hunting.

23:33.027 --> 23:35.250
I didn't have any camo or a gun or

23:35.586 --> 23:36.507
or any knowledge.

23:36.587 --> 23:42.115
And we went early that morning and we was driving out into a field and we stopped.

23:42.615 --> 23:43.396
He said, get out.

23:45.299 --> 23:46.180
He said, walk that way.

23:46.220 --> 23:47.422
There's a tree stand down there.

23:49.405 --> 23:50.206
And I walked that way.

23:50.266 --> 23:50.967
I couldn't find it.

23:51.307 --> 23:53.009
And I walked some more and I finally found it.

23:54.652 --> 23:59.178
And it was a tree stand sitting there and he told me he said, calm about 10 to 15 feet in that tree.

24:00.039 --> 24:01.521
Well, I never used a tree stand before.

24:02.222 --> 24:05.426
I was scared, but I figured it out.

24:07.714 --> 24:11.298
Jay Besh was weak.

24:11.318 --> 24:12.699
They inherited their weakness.

24:12.779 --> 24:20.688
It made them weak physically, but also they made them weak spiritually.

24:24.152 --> 24:27.335
I didn't inherit a daddy who read me the Bible.

24:28.577 --> 24:32.481
I didn't inherit a daddy who showed me how to be a spiritual leader.

24:33.862 --> 24:37.266
I didn't inherit a daddy who showed me how to love his wife like Christ loved the church.

24:39.362 --> 24:44.650
I believe my daddy is a good person, but spiritually speaking, I inherited weakness.

24:45.492 --> 24:46.433
And it made me weak.

24:47.535 --> 24:52.482
And I had to seek somebody who was strong to help me.

24:54.405 --> 24:56.008
I want to make weak people strong.

24:57.450 --> 25:00.996
I'm going to need strong people when I get weak.

25:01.356 --> 25:07.666
Because of the strong soul in Israel, the weak have in turn become the deliverers.

25:13.250 --> 25:14.572
I'm going to need strong people.

25:15.093 --> 25:21.281
We, we, we turned back over to, to 1 Samuel, chapter 31.

25:21.481 --> 25:35.180
In verse 11, it says, and when the inhabitants of J. Bescud heard of that, which the Philistines had done to Saul, all the valiant men arose.

25:36.041 --> 25:37.243
And they went all night.

25:38.925 --> 25:39.806
They went all night.

25:39.846 --> 25:40.627
They didn't care.

25:40.687 --> 25:42.610
They knew somebody was weak.

25:42.882 --> 25:45.786
and they were strong and they needed, they needed to help them out.

25:46.206 --> 25:54.658
They went all night, they took the body, the saw on the bodies and the suns from the wall of this shin, and they came out and burned them and they took their bones and they buried them under that tree in J-Bish.

25:56.400 --> 26:01.787
There are just some areas of which are stronger than others.

26:03.529 --> 26:10.098
Everybody has something in their life which you're stronger than somebody else.

26:11.778 --> 26:13.740
You may have the gift of being a singer.

26:14.902 --> 26:17.505
How many of us here don't?

26:17.525 --> 26:19.167
You may be not an auto mechanic.

26:20.388 --> 26:21.329
How many of us aren't?

26:22.651 --> 26:23.632
You may be a plumber.

26:24.232 --> 26:25.093
Everybody here is.

26:28.918 --> 26:30.780
And if you're not a plumber, I can help you out.

26:30.960 --> 26:33.463
Quarter inch of foot, there you're a plumber.

26:35.986 --> 26:37.388
Some people can play instruments.

26:38.909 --> 26:39.570
Others can't.

26:42.242 --> 26:52.093
But many of us, I promise, you're made in such a unique way that there's something that you can do better than so many others.

26:53.174 --> 26:54.275
And you're strong in it.

26:56.218 --> 27:00.322
But what is it that God wants you to do with the strength that He's given you?

27:01.884 --> 27:07.410
He wants you to use your strength to help those that are weak.

27:10.402 --> 27:16.149
You better help those that are weak because the day may come when you are weak.

27:16.169 --> 27:20.053
You are going to need them because they have become strong.

27:21.235 --> 27:29.064
Romans 15, one says, we then that are strong ought to bear the infirmities of the weak, not to please ourselves.

27:30.786 --> 27:34.971
If you would turn over to 2 Samuel, I'm about done.

27:34.991 --> 27:37.874
2 Samuel chapter number two.

27:43.394 --> 28:08.472
verse four, and the men of Judah came and there they in order David, king over the house of Judah, and they told David saying, the men of J. Beshgiliad were they that buried Saul, and David sent messengers into the men of J. Beshgiliad and said to them, blessed be ye of the Lord, they have showed this kindness unto your Lord, even unto Saul, and have buried him.

28:09.313 --> 28:12.658
And now the Lord showed kindness and truth unto you, and I will also

28:14.242 --> 28:19.228
require you this kindness because you have done this thing.

28:20.170 --> 28:28.360
Therefore, now let your hands be strengthened and be you valiant for your master of souls dead and also the house of you to have anointing me king over them.

28:28.380 --> 28:30.643
Man, thank God for Saul.

28:31.224 --> 28:32.225
Thank God for Israel.

28:32.245 --> 28:34.308
They deliver J. Bish Gilead.

28:38.093 --> 28:42.258
They were weak, but the day is going to come when David is going to say thank God for J. Bish.

28:43.842 --> 28:45.123
that was delivered by Saul.

28:46.004 --> 28:51.330
Because the day has come when the weak have become strong and the strong have needed them.

28:51.850 --> 28:54.953
You may be strong, but beloved, we are all prone to weakness.

28:55.554 --> 29:02.101
And in our weakness, if we have aided those who have been down, they'll help us.

29:03.863 --> 29:06.625
Ms. Tan, if you would have come get a song.

29:08.027 --> 29:11.090
I was thinking about, you probably heard this before, about Thomas Edison.

29:12.802 --> 29:14.325
when he was trying to make the light bulb.

29:15.406 --> 29:17.870
He failed over and over and over and over again.

29:17.930 --> 29:19.753
Thousands of experiments didn't work.

29:20.695 --> 29:26.244
And a reporter once asked him how it felt to fail so many times.

29:27.246 --> 29:29.269
An innocent reply, I haven't failed.

29:30.030 --> 29:32.074
I just found 10,000 ways that wouldn't work.

29:33.115 --> 29:39.506
Those trials that we face when we're weak can lead to a bright future.

29:41.090 --> 29:45.795
Some of us are standing today where Jay Bechgile had once stood.

29:47.877 --> 29:49.198
You feel like you're surrounded.

29:50.099 --> 29:51.120
The pressure is heavy.

29:52.241 --> 29:53.382
The strength is gone.

29:54.343 --> 29:57.887
You've prayed, but the answer just hasn't yet come.

29:58.968 --> 30:03.973
And quietly in your heart, you wonder, am I going to make it?

30:05.374 --> 30:06.355
I want you to hear this.

30:06.495 --> 30:09.138
God has not abandoned you.

30:09.794 --> 30:17.406
The moment of weakness may be the very place where his power is getting ready to be revealed.

30:18.848 --> 30:25.599
When you're ready to come to him and admit your weakness, he stands with his arms wide open.

30:27.662 --> 30:29.766
Others of us may be in seasons of strength.

30:29.846 --> 30:37.458
Things are going well, doors are opening, life feels stable, but the danger is subtle.

30:38.722 --> 30:44.856
You may be drifting from the same dependence that once kept you close to God.

30:45.838 --> 30:48.825
Strength must never replace surrender.

30:50.408 --> 30:56.402
Today God's calling both the weak and the strong to the same place.

